00:09:37.034 --> 00:09:38.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who is she?

148
00:09:38.744 --> 00:09:40.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know, don't you?

149
00:09:40.371 --> 00:09:41.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

150
00:09:41.998 --> 00:09:44.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is there some kind of connection
between this person

151
00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:46.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and Keith turning himself in?

152
00:09:46.877 --> 00:09:49.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What exactly is he
trying to accomplish?

153
00:09:50.464 --> 00:09:52.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He wants answers.

154
00:09:53.009 --> 00:09:56.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Eight winters ago, the poor girl
was sliced up from head to toe.

155
00:09:56.887 --> 00:09:58.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She was dumped in the mountains.

156
00:09:58.931 --> 00:10:01.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was Keith's little sister
they found there.

157
00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:09.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So that gold solution
is a necessary component

158
00:10:09.817 --> 00:10:12.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in the reuse
of discarded Reggies, isn't it?

159
00:10:12.486 --> 00:10:13.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've heard it's what they use

160
00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:16.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to regulate their testosterone
and dopamine levels.

161
00:10:16.657 --> 00:10:18.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There seem to be
various kinds of it,

162
00:10:18.784 --> 00:10:20.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but that's all I'm aware of.

163
00:10:20.453 --> 00:10:23.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why are Reggies discarded?

164
00:10:23.414 --> 00:10:26.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Around age 20, their powers
start to go out of control,

165
00:10:26.459 --> 00:10:28.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and they lose the ability
to think rationally.

166
00:10:28.878 --> 00:10:31.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fall below a set value,
and you're discarded.

167
00:10:31.380 --> 00:10:35.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
By "discarded," you mean
released into society at large.

168
00:10:35.509 --> 00:10:36.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah.

169
00:10:37.845 --> 00:10:39.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How many are there, anyway?

170
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:42.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Grade-C goods like Kyle, I mean.

171
00:10:42.224 --> 00:10:43.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lots of 'em.

172
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:45.311 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This country is crawling

173
00:10:45.394 --> 00:10:48.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
with more discarded Reggies
than you can imagine,

174
00:10:48.314 --> 00:10:50.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and with just one signal,

175
00:10:50.483 --> 00:10:52.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
they'll transform
into frenzied weapons...

176
00:10:53.069 --> 00:10:55.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lily] <i>It's disguised</i>
<i>as something else,</i>

177
00:10:55.196 --> 00:10:56.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>so even though</i>
<i>it's in plain sight,</i>

178
00:10:56.947 --> 00:10:58.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>no one can see it.</i>

179
00:10:58.240 --> 00:11:00.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The only way to stop them
is to kill them.

180
00:11:02.370 --> 00:11:04.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Keith] Let's go buy
some red-bean buns.

181
00:11:04.455 --> 00:11:05.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

182
00:11:08.626 --> 00:11:10.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[overlapping chatter]

183
00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:20.429 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm only answering questions
about the investigation.

184
00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:24.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have issues with the direction
this investigation is going in!

185
00:11:24.266 --> 00:11:26.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm busy. Come back later.

186
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:27.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Lily grunts]

187
00:11:28.062 --> 00:11:29.522 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We could
keep doing this forever,

188
00:11:29.605 --> 00:11:32.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but it won't bring us
any closer to finding Keith.

189
00:11:32.108 --> 00:11:34.026 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get back to work.
That's an order.

190
00:11:34.110 --> 00:11:35.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I refuse.

191
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:36.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fine. Then get out.

192
00:11:36.695 --> 00:11:37.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?!

193
00:11:38.072 --> 00:11:39.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're just in the way here.

194
00:11:39.615 --> 00:11:41.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Leave your badge, and get out.

195
00:11:41.158 --> 00:11:42.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?!

196
00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:45.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Didn't you hear me?
You're suspended.

197
00:11:45.496 --> 00:11:47.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[gasping]
-I don't have the time or need

198
00:11:47.748 --> 00:11:49.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for idiots
who can't obey orders.

199
00:11:49.625 --> 00:11:52.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You're dismissed.
-[grunts]

200
00:11:54.380 --> 00:11:56.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Lily] Drop dead,
you four-eyed chin with legs!

201
00:11:56.799 --> 00:12:00.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bet you didn't know everyone
here calls you that, dumb-ass!

202
00:12:02.805 --> 00:12:04.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Eric, it's me.

203
00:12:04.515 --> 00:12:06.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lily's on the move.

204
00:12:06.475 --> 00:12:08.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you sure
this is a good idea?

205
00:12:08.727 --> 00:12:10.354 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm getting kinda worried.

206
00:12:10.438 --> 00:12:12.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The R.I.S. is under
Market Maker surveillance.

207
00:12:12.898 --> 00:12:16.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we want to find a way
to get ahead of them,

208
00:12:16.193 --> 00:12:17.862 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
this is the only option we have.

209
00:12:17.945 --> 00:12:20.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Which is all well and good,</i>
<i>but Lily getting caught</i>

210
00:12:20.448 --> 00:12:22.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>in the crossfire</i>
<i>is my main concern.</i>

211
00:12:22.199 --> 00:12:23.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
METAMORPHISM?
MARKET MAKER

212
00:12:23.242 --> 00:12:24.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Boris, she's a professional.

213
00:12:25.035 --> 00:12:26.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
SYSTEM REBUILD IS IMPERATIVE
KAELA

214
00:12:26.454 --> 00:12:28.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sure that you've
realized it by now,

215
00:12:28.456 --> 00:12:30.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but Lily and Keith
are two of a kind.

216
00:12:30.708 --> 00:12:31.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
COMMANDO TEAM NECESSARY
LILY

217
00:12:31.750 --> 00:12:32.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They have similar
thought processes,

218
00:12:33.043 --> 00:12:36.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
drive, and inquiring minds.

219
00:12:36.422 --> 00:12:38.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's a reason
I scouted Lily for the R.I.S.

220
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:41.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
over everyone's objections.

221
00:12:41.177 --> 00:12:44.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Deep down, she has abilities
on par with Keith's.

222
00:12:44.805 --> 00:12:46.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I sensed it about her.

223
00:12:48.225 --> 00:12:51.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Boris, if Keith
doesn't want to be found,

224
00:12:51.228 --> 00:12:52.897 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I won't be able to find him.

225
00:12:53.981 --> 00:12:55.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>It's up to Lily.</i>

226
00:12:57.985 --> 00:12:59.445 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Okay.</i>

227
00:13:13.375 --> 00:13:14.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kaela, are you done?

228
00:13:15.044 --> 00:13:16.962 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Almost there.

229
00:13:17.046 --> 00:13:18.506 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
'Kay, all done!

230
00:13:28.432 --> 00:13:29.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is everything all secure now?

231
00:13:29.975 --> 00:13:32.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not sure yet,
but at the very least,

232
00:13:32.228 --> 00:13:33.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
this'll keep 'em out
for a while.

233
00:13:36.941 --> 00:13:39.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Here.
This red line is Lily, right?

234
00:13:40.819 --> 00:13:42.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm curious.
Who tagged her car?

235
00:13:42.821 --> 00:13:44.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Boris did.

236
00:13:44.198 --> 00:13:46.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She's gonna be pissed
when she finds out.

237
00:13:46.283 --> 00:13:48.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I had to.
She doesn't have what it takes

238
00:13:48.869 --> 00:13:50.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to keep up an act for long.

239
00:13:50.663 --> 00:13:52.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah, I bet
you're right about that.

240
00:13:52.748 --> 00:13:54.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[together]
She's such an idiot.

241
00:13:54.750 --> 00:13:57.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[music playing]

242
00:14:09.974 --> 00:14:11.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[no audible dialogue]

243
00:14:27.533 --> 00:14:29.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I want a red-bean bun.

244
00:14:29.952 --> 00:14:31.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

245
00:14:33.038 --> 00:14:35.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't have
a single lead to go on.

246
00:14:35.416 --> 00:14:39.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No matter where I go,
the results are always the same.

247
00:14:39.587 --> 00:14:41.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What the heck?

248
00:14:41.463 --> 00:14:42.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I should have gone someplace

249
00:14:42.798 --> 00:14:45.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
where the food
was good, at least. Hmm?

250
00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:52.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn't that the smell
of those funny-tasting spices?

251
00:15:05.696 --> 00:15:09.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
HOLS ISLAND

252
00:15:12.536 --> 00:15:14.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Koku] How did you figure out

253
00:15:14.121 --> 00:15:16.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that blue steel
was the Reggies' weakness?

254
00:15:17.708 --> 00:15:20.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Keith] Same as you, I suppose.

255
00:15:21.086 --> 00:15:22.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My old man's journal.

256
00:15:27.051 --> 00:15:29.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How long do you plan to keep
wandering around aimlessly?

257
00:15:32.056 --> 00:15:33.557 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hate to disappoint you,

258
00:15:33.641 --> 00:15:35.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but there's nothing aimless
about it.

259
00:15:35.392 --> 00:15:38.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're hitting up towns
that have good places to eat.

260
00:15:38.145 --> 00:15:39.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My question was how long?

261
00:15:39.521 --> 00:15:41.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Until you're back at 100%.

262
00:15:41.941 --> 00:15:45.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you've got time to gab,
rub one out, and go to sleep.

263
00:15:50.407 --> 00:15:53.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You seem pretty much recovered.

264
00:15:53.410 --> 00:15:55.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looks like
you're good to fight already.

265
00:15:57.122 --> 00:15:59.041 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm guessing you have
an ulterior motive

266
00:15:59.124 --> 00:16:00.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for saving my life.

267
00:16:00.626 --> 00:16:02.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it?

268
00:16:05.923 --> 00:16:08.092 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's something
I want your help with.

269
00:16:09.259 --> 00:16:11.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's no reason for me
to help you with anything.

270
00:16:12.012 --> 00:16:13.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's where you're wrong.

271
00:16:13.555 --> 00:16:15.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would you mind getting this
out of my face?

272
00:16:15.891 --> 00:16:16.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can't see.

273
00:16:25.734 --> 00:16:27.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I demand an explanation.

274
00:16:28.779 --> 00:16:29.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen...

275
00:16:29.863 --> 00:16:32.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been digging up dirt
on two men.

276
00:16:32.116 --> 00:16:34.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's the reason
I got back into the field.

277
00:16:34.743 --> 00:16:37.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>I needed to see everything</i>
<i>with my own two eyes.</i>

278
00:16:41.667 --> 00:16:43.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That road will lead her
to Hols Island.

279
00:16:43.919 --> 00:16:47.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I can't imagine Keith would have
gone to a location like that.

280
00:16:47.131 --> 00:16:49.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah, it's full
of old men and women,

281
00:16:49.133 --> 00:16:51.051 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
not to mention tourist traps.

282
00:16:51.135 --> 00:16:53.053 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Keith would stand out
like a sore thumb

283
00:16:53.137 --> 00:16:54.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if he set foot outside.

284
00:16:54.722 --> 00:16:56.265 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
KEITH'S GOAL ISN'T ESCAPE.

285
00:16:56.348 --> 00:16:59.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Kaela, make arrangements
for a chopper.

286
00:17:01.353 --> 00:17:04.481 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Keith] <i>I've spent a very</i>
<i>long time looking into them,</i>

287
00:17:04.565 --> 00:17:08.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>but no matter how deep I dig,</i>
<i>clues that almost seem made up</i>

288
00:17:08.527 --> 00:17:10.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>keep getting in the way</i>
<i>of the truth.</i>

289
00:17:10.529 --> 00:17:11.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you mean?

290
00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:14.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, things like
the possibility

291
00:17:14.908 --> 00:17:16.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of nonhumans
roaming around the world...

292
00:17:17.995 --> 00:17:19.455 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in other words, you guys.

293
00:17:19.538 --> 00:17:21.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You still
don't seem to get this,

294
00:17:21.415 --> 00:17:23.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but Yuna and I are not Reggies.

295
00:17:23.417 --> 00:17:26.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm starving.
